sticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  .hackINFECTION</span><hr size=1> So it's out!  Yay!  And based on an excellent anime!  So I'm wondering - has anyone played it and can therefore answer me this:  Is it worth buying? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=themightyservo>The Mighty Servo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(2/22/03 9:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=610.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://filebox.vt.edu/users/cmayer/images/servo.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: .hackINFECTION</span><hr size=1> I've played the demo...and my roommate played through the game. I've also seen .hack//SIGN, and enjoyed it. The game is very true to the anime. If you like that, you'll feel like you're in it. The downside is that the game isn't all that long (I think my roomie said 17 hours), and according to reviews from experts, is &quot;average&quot; not stellar. I dunno, I though it was pretty fun...but yeah, not Chrono Trigger or anything. <br>
Comes with .hack//LIMINALITY episode 1 too, which is decent...and adds value. <br>
<br>
I haven't bought it myself yet, mostly because I already have a few RPGs that I've barely played...and I'm having too much fun with Guilty Gear XX. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kyojiogami>kyoji Ogami</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(2/26/03 9:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=610.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.liquid2k.com/kyojiogami/KO.jpg height=111 width=127></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: .hackINFECTION</span><hr size=1> HAHA!  Yes...it is too awesome for words.  I've had the game for 3 days and I'm already hooked.<br>
<br>
It may just be me...I love RPGs and I've been waiting for a game like this for years.  <br>
<br>
The Good -<br>
1. The graphics are nice.  -mmm, Blackrose-<br>
<br>
2. I'm loving the soundtrack.  The first operating system music get a bit redundant...but you get new stuff rather quickly.<br>
<br>
3. Controls are a bit disorienting at first...but you get the hang of them in no time.  In fact, it becomes one of the games best qualities.  Total control of your character and special abilities and magic...without the confusion of a game like Kingdom Hearts.<br>
 <br>
4. When your character passes out, your party members can resurrect you ^.^<br>
<br>
5. Your choice of English dub or Japanese w/ subtitles<br>
<br>
The Bad -<br>
1. It takes about 45 minutes to get through the opening tutorials.<br>
<br>
2. Some of the characters get old really fast *but, hey, stop adding them to your party <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> *<br>
<br>
3. The weapons/abilities thing is a tad complicated.<br>
<br>
<br>
Other than that...GO BUY THE GAME.  IT'S FREAKIN AWESOME!!! <p><br>
